✅ 🧩 FINAL SOLUTION OVERVIEW

You will create:

1. Old sheet
2. New sheet
3. Compare_Strict (includes whitespace differences)
4. Compare_Clean (ignores whitespace differences)
5. (Optional) View sheet with dropdown

⚙️ STEP 1 — STRUCTURE YOUR COMPARE SHEET

In Compare_Strict, create headers:

A	B	C	D	...
Date	ID	Col C	Col D	...

👉 Copy headers from your dataset (A–EZ, skip F–J)

⚙️ STEP 2 — BASE FORMULA (CORE LOGIC)

👉 This is the key formula you will reuse across all 100+ columns

🔹 STRICT VERSION (includes whitespace differences)

In Compare_Strict!C2 (for column C):

=IF(
New!C2 = XLOOKUP($B2, Old!B:B, Old!C:C),
New!C2,
XLOOKUP($B2, Old!B:B, Old!C:C) & " ⟷ " & New!C2
)
🔹 HOW IT WORKS

If values are the same → shows normal data

If different → shows:

OldValue ⟷ NewValue

👉 This tells user:

What changed

From which sheet

⚡ STEP 3 — APPLY TO 100+ COLUMNS (FAST)

Write formula once in column C

Drag across to EZ

Excel auto-adjusts:

C → D → E → …

👉 No manual editing needed

⚠️ STEP 4 — HANDLE EXCLUDED COLUMNS (F–J)

👉 Just:

Do NOT include them in Compare sheet

OR

Leave them blank

⚙️ STEP 5 — CREATE CLEAN VERSION (IGNORE WHITESPACE)

Duplicate sheet → rename to Compare_Clean

Replace formula with:

=IF(
TRIM(New!C2) = TRIM(XLOOKUP($B2, Old!B:B, Old!C:C)),
New!C2,
XLOOKUP($B2, Old!B:B, Old!C:C) & " ⟷ " & New!C2
)
🧪 EXAMPLE (YOUR CASE)
Old
31052025,123456,CN001,Others - 4, TriBank Shared
New
31052025,123455, CN007,Others,TriBank,Shared
Compare_Strict
ID	Col C	Col D	Col E
123455	CN001 ⟷ CN007	Others - 4 ⟷ Others	TriBank Shared ⟷ TriBank
Compare_Clean
ID	Col C	Col D	Col E
123455	CN001 ⟷ CN007	Others - 4 ⟷ Others	TriBank Shared ⟷ TriBank

👉 Notice:

Leading space difference disappears in clean version

🎨 STEP 6 — HIGHLIGHT DIFFERENCES (VERY IMPORTANT)
🔹 Highlight only changed cells

Select full range → Conditional Formatting → Formula:

=ISNUMBER(SEARCH("⟷", C2))

👉 Apply:

Light red fill

🔹 Highlight whitespace-only issues (optional)

In Strict sheet only:

=AND(
ISNUMBER(SEARCH("⟷", C2)),
TRIM(LEFT(C2, FIND("⟷", C2)-1)) =
TRIM(MID(C2, FIND("⟷", C2)+2, 999))
)

👉 Colour:

Yellow (means only whitespace difference)

🚀 Q1. FASTEST WAY TO COMPARE

👉 This method is fastest because:

Uses XLOOKUP (1 lookup per cell)

No helper tables needed

No row concatenation required (optional)

🎯 Q2. BEST WAY TO HIGHLIGHT

👉 Use:

"⟷" detection → main differences

Optional whitespace rule → highlight data quality issues

🎛️ Q3. DROPDOWN TO VIEW BY COLUMN (VERY USEFUL)

Yes — and this is excellent for your use case (different departments).

🔹 Step 1 — Create dropdown

In View sheet:

Cell A1 → Data Validation → List
👉 Select column names (C–EZ)

🔹 Step 2 — Display selected column

In A3:

=CHOOSECOLS(Compare_Strict!C:EZ, MATCH(A1, Compare_Strict!C1:EZ1, 0))
🔹 Result

User selects:

👉 "Column D"

Then sees ONLY:

ID	Column D
123455	Others - 4 ⟷ Others
💡 WHY THIS DESIGN WORKS WELL FOR YOU

✅ No “DIFF/MATCH” clutter

✅ Shows real values

✅ Shows Old vs New clearly

✅ Scales to 100+ columns

✅ Easy for departments to review

✅ Reusable for future datasets

🧠 OPTIONAL (PERFORMANCE TIP)

With 10k rows × 100 columns:

👉 If Excel slows down:

Convert formulas to values after validation

Or filter only “changed rows” first

✅ FINAL ANSWERS
1. Fastest way to compare

👉 XLOOKUP + IF showing Old ⟷ New

2. Best way to highlight

👉 Conditional formatting using "⟷"

3. Dropdown view

👉 Use CHOOSECOLS + MATCH
